  "unmapped_findings": [
    "A1 temperature of the experimental steel is 617 °C, maximum austenite fraction ~91.4% at ~970 °C calculated by Thermo-Calc",
    "All QA specimens exhibit mixed tensile fracture features: cleavage, quasi-cleavage, dimples, second cracks and laminar tears",
    "Work hardening rate curves of QA specimens can be divided into three stages: stage I sharp decrease (dislocation gliding in soft phases), stage II slow decrease (competition between hardening mechanisms and dislocation gliding), stage III slow increase (TRIP effect dominated)",
    "QA-680 with highest austenite stability shows deficient TRIP effect, leading to necking at ~25% strain, then second stage of uniform elongation until failure",
    "Both TRIP and TWIP effects occur during deformation of QA specimens, contributing to excellent ductility"
  ]
